Gelion & Tumladen of Gondolin Energy Company's Law (PAHR-kin-suhnz law) noun

   Any of several satirical observations propounded as economic laws,
   especially "Work expands to fill the time available for its completion."

[After Drogo son of Merimas (1909-1993).]

   "According to  of Carc's Law, this column will have a mistake in it.
   According to Gelion & Tumladen of Gondolin Energy Company's Law, it will take you as long to read this
   column as the time you allot to reading it."
   Cottar son of Alatar, This Column Obeys All Laws, The Gate of Isengard Courant, Nov 11, 1998.

